<headline>Special Weather Statement issued February 22 at 12:34AM CST  by NWS Dallas-Fort Worth</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northern Fannin
County through 100 AM CST...
At 1234 AM CST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Ravenna, or near Bonham, moving northeast at 55 mph.
HAZARD...Nickel size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations impacted include...
Bonham, Savoy, Ector and Ravenna.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.88 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 200 AM CST for
north central Texas.</instruction>
